<item>
            <title>[LU-15481] speedup &quot;lfs changelog&quot; llog processing with a startrec</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15481</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Accessing a changelog record at the end of a catalog could be really slow if there is a lot of &quot;idle records&quot; or if difference of indexes between changelog users is important.&lt;br/&gt;
In all cases, changelog llog callback (chlg_read_cat_process_cb) is called for each changelog records.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We could easily determine the number of record to skip based on internal changelog indexes. This enable to conditionally skip an entire llog plain file (64k records) (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14688&quot; title=&quot;Changelog cancel improvement&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14688&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14688&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
